    "freetext": "sexual harassment is a highly troubling gendered phenomenon that plagues young women on a daily basis. the way in which sexual harassment is perceived and treated is varied and is largely based on racial and class stereotypes. this paper highlights the findings from a study in which a group of middle and high school teachers were interviewed and their perceptions of sexual harassment on their campuses were discussed. what was revealed throughout this study was the way in which many teachers' notions of sexuality are conceptualised through their notions of class and race. this paper addresses how such racial and class stereotypes veil the sexual victimisation of many young women. rahimi, regina and liston, delores d. 2011 race, class, and emerging sexuality: teacher perceptions and sexual harassment in schools ethnizit\\\"at // ethnicity;lehrer*innen // teachers;m\\\"adchen // girls;mobbing // bullying;sexuelle bel\\\"astigung // sexual harassment;soziale ungleichheit und/oder gerechtigkeit // social inequality and/or justice 799-810 23 7 0954-0253 gender and education 10.1080/09540253.2010.536143 article    rahimi, r. and d. liston r. rahimi, d. liston rahimi and liston rahimi, r. and d. liston rahimi &amp; liston"
